President Obama encourages all Kenyans to reflect on the progress their country has made since the post-election violence three years ago. He commends their efforts in reconciling communities, reforming institutions, and seeking lasting peace and prosperity. He believes that Kenya is moving towards an era of accountability and equal opportunity, away from impunity and divisionism. President Obama urges all Kenyan leaders and citizens to cooperate with the International Criminal Court (ICC) investigation and focus on implementing reforms for the future of the nation. He emphasizes that those found responsible for crimes will be held accountable as individuals, without singling out any community for shame. Lastly, President Obama assures Kenyans that the United States will continue to support them as a friend and partner.